deployment/ceph-ansible/ceph-osd.yaml.message:
I have been comparing both blocks in the upgrade tasks and post_upgrade_tasks and unless I missed something, it looks like the only different thing between blocks is the with_items section. Why not using this https://www.reddit.com/r/ansible/comments/99ymjf/can_i_use_with_items_with_conditional_of_each_item/ instead of duplicating the whole block twice?

The idea would be to leave the code as it was initially and modify only the Set noout flag and Unset noout flag:

shell: {{ container_client }} exec -u root ceph-mon-${HOSTNAME%%.*} ceph osd set {{ item.flag }}"
when: "item.when"
with_items:
    - { flag: noout, when: true }
    - { flag: norecover, when: true }
    - { flag: nobackfill, when: true }
    - { flag: norebalance,when: true }
    - { flag: nodeep-scrub, when: not allinone_upgrade }
    - { flag: nodown, when: allinone_upgrade }
    - { flag: pause, when: allinone_upgrade }

I also bet that it would be possible to use jinja2 templating to conditionally create the list of whith_items, something like:

with_items:
    - noout
    - norecover
    - nobackfill
    - norebalance
    {% if all_inone_upgrade %}
    - nodown
    - pause
    {% else %}
    - nodeep-scrub
    {% endif %}

There might be many other approaches...but the idea is to avoid duplicating so many tasks, if possible.
